    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill amends the Secure Rural Schools and Community Self-Determination Act of 2000 to modify the authorized uses of funds a county elects to receive under such Act to include:</p> <ul> <li> reimbursing the county for law enforcement patrols and evacuations that are performed on federal land;</li> <li>search and rescue preparedness training; and </li> <li>capital equipment, equipment maintenance, and other purchases related to carrying out search and rescue and other emergency services. </li> </ul>  <p>A participating county may reallocate funds received under such Act for a different use than authorized under such Act only after the 45-day public comment period has ended, at the beginning of which the county shall publish in any publications of local record a proposal that describes how the county proposes to use such funds. </p> <p>The bill extends the authority for the initiation of county projects until the end of FY2019 and provides for county funds to remain available until expended. </p>]]></text>
